snippet.textDisplay: On a sentimental visit to Pakistan  in March 2018 each time the  public transport crossed  the  Chenab River bridge I would   invariably think of this melody  and  the tragedy of the young , love - struck  lady who  was swept away  by its strong currents a long time ago. .

snippet.textDisplay: No one makes music like this anymore.... serene and meaningful. Loved the lady playing the Sitar (!?!). The 'yaar nu milegi ajj  laash yaar di' (Laash is a weird word for me) should have sounded very bad being repeated so many times but listening to it again, it kinda fits with what comes later. Very well done! The third person kinda spoils it towards the end but maybe he's the voice of advice and reason but he's a bit rubbish lol.  I also very much dislike the sentence 'Pharr pallrra -pakkay murshid- da'... maybe '-sacchay murshid-' would have sounded better to my ears... His voice also flops at 'Jeyraaa'.... But overall really enjoyed the song.
